  }
];

const faqs = [
  {
    question: "Do I need a Facebook Business page for my security firm?",
    answer: "Messenger functions through a linked Facebook Business page. Security installers posting CCTV footage comparison shots — old grainy analogue versus new crystal-clear 4K IP — structured cabling installations with colour-coded Cat6 at the patch panel, and timelapse alarm panel commissionings attract outstanding engagement from building managers who immediately recognise the upgrade their own premises require."
  },
  {
    question: "What security enquiries come through Messenger?",
    answer: "Homeowners afraid after a neighbour's break-in who want cameras and a monitored alarm. Shop owners needing CCTV after repeated shoplifting. Facilities managers wanting to switch their annual maintenance contract to an NSI-approved firm. Property developers needing security packages for show homes. Pub landlords seeking cameras after anti-social behaviour incidents. Each sender has studied your approved installation standard."
  },
  {
    question: "How fast does the AI reply to security messages?",
    answer: "Messenger responses generate within seconds. Facebook's activity indicator confirms your security firm actively monitors. A shop owner whose premises were broken into last night — glass everywhere, police crime scene tape still up, insurer demanding immediate CCTV evidence — needs an instant, competent response from an NSI-approved installer, not a page that last updated two months ago."
  },
  {
    question: "What does Messenger cost for security contractors?",
    answer: `The Facebook Messenger add-on costs £${pricing.addOn.price}/month. A domestic alarm and CCTV installation generates £1,500 to £4,000. One homeowner's post-burglary system — alarm, cameras, video doorbell, and ARC monitoring — initiated by a Messenger message after she saw your neighbour's installation on Facebook — covers the annual channel cost from a single job.`
  },
  {
    question: "Can I continue Messenger conversations personally?",
    answer: "Post one reply in any thread and the AI hands over permanently. Most security engineers let the AI collect the initial specification — property type, existing security, crime context, monitoring requirement, and camera count — then take over to discuss camera positions, alarm zones, and the survey visit."
  },
  {
    question: "How is Messenger data from security queries protected?",
    answer: "All Messenger conversations — premises photographs, alarm configurations, CCTV positions, access control layouts, vulnerability details, and sender contact information — are encrypted and stored on UK and EU servers under UK GDPR. Data flows exclusively to you. No security details reach competitors or third-party lead platforms."
